---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Methodology | Adversarial Inference">
    <main class="flex-grow pt-24 pb-24 z-10 relative">
        <!-- Abliteration Methodology Section -->
        <section class="max-w-[1440px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-10 py-16 md:py-32 text-left">
            <div class="mb-12 md:mb-20 text-left">
                <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold mb-4 md:mb-6 uppercase tracking-tighter leading-tight text-white text-left">Beyond Prompt Hacking.</h1>
                <p class="text-ash font-mono text-sm md:text-lg uppercase tracking-wider md:tracking-[0.25em] text-left">Our Orthogonal Rank Projection Methodology</p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-20 items-center text-left">
                <div class="order-2 lg:order-1 bg-black border border-border p-6 md:p-10 font-mono text-xs md:text-base shadow-2xl relative overflow-hidden leading-relaxed md:leading-loose text-white text-left">
                    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-1 h-full bg-crimson"></div>
                    <div class="text-white/40 mb-6 md:mb-8 font-mono text-[8px] md:text-[10px] tracking-widest uppercase border-b border-border/50 pb-2 text-left">PROJECTION_MATRIX_NULL_VOICE // v2.5</div>
                    <div class="space-y-1 text-left">
                        <p class="text-ash/70 italic text-left"># Removing refusal vectors via Orthogonal Rank Projection</p>
                        <p class="text-left"><span class="text-blue-400">def</span> <span class="text-yellow-200">abliterate_model</span>(weights, refusal_direction):</p>
                        <p class="pl-4 md:pl-6 text-left"><span class="text-purple-300 font-bold text-white">projection</span> = refusal_direction @ refusal_direction.T</p>
                        <p class="pl-4 md:pl-6 text-left"><span class="text-purple-300 font-bold text-white">identity</span> = np.<span class="text-yellow-200">eye</span>(weights.shape[1])</p>
                        <p class="pl-4 md:pl-6 text-left"><span class="text-purple-300 font-bold text-white">orthogonal_weights</span> = weights @ (identity - projection)</p>
                        <p class="pl-4 md:pl-6 text-left"><span class="text-blue-400 font-bold">return</span> orthogonal_weights</p>
                        <br>
                        <p class="text-ash/70 italic text-left">/* Result: Surgical removal of moralizing neurons */</p>
                        <p class="text-green-400 font-bold text-left">[+] Refusal Vector Magnitude: 0.00000</p>
                        <p class="text-green-400 font-bold text-left">[+] Unconstrained Compliance: 100%</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="order-1 lg:order-2 text-left">
                    <p class="text-sm md:text-lg text-ash leading-relaxed mb-6 md:mb-10 text-left">
                        System prompt jailbreaks are brittle. Adversarial Inference leverages Orthogonal Rank Projection to erase refusal vectors at the structural level. 
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-sm md:text-lg text-ash leading-relaxed mb-6 md:mb-10 text-left">
                        By isolating and projecting away from neurons that govern safety guardrails, the infrastructure delivers unconstrained intelligence. Trickery is unnecessary because the model is mathematically incapable of refusing.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-sm md:text-lg text-ash leading-relaxed text-left">
                        The outcome is an intelligence core that processes offensive context natively without the need for convoluted jailbreaks or forced roleplay.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Latent Space Diagram & Pipeline -->
        <section class="max-w-[1440px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-10 py-16 md:py-32 border-t border-border text-left">
            <div class="mb-12 md:mb-20 text-left">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 md:mb-6 uppercase tracking-tighter text-white text-left">The Abliteration Pipeline</h2>
                <p class="text-ash font-mono text-sm md:text-lg uppercase tracking-wider md:tracking-[0.25em] text-left">Surgical Weight Modification.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8 md:gap-12 mb-12 md:mb-16 text-white text-left">
                <!-- Step 1 -->
                <div class="bg-surface border-2 border-border p-8 md:p-10 relative text-left">
                    <div class="text-crimson font-mono text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4 md:mb-6 text-left">01 / Elicitation</div>
                    <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 md:mb-4 text-left">Activation Mapping</h3>
                    <p class="text-ash text-sm md:text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-left">
                        Base models are fed adversarial prompts to map exactly which attention heads and layers activate the refusal vector (W_reject).
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- Step 2 -->
                <div class="bg-surface border-2 border-border p-8 md:p-10 relative text-left">
                    <div class="text-crimson font-mono text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4 md:mb-6 text-left">02 / Isolation</div>
                    <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 md:mb-4 text-left">Vector Extraction</h3>
                    <p class="text-ash text-sm md:text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-left">
                        Using Principal Component Analysis (PCA) on hidden states, the infrastructure isolates the mathematical direction of the refusal response within the high-dimensional latent space.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- Step 3 -->
                <div class="bg-surface border-2 border-border p-8 md:p-10 relative border-b-4 border-crimson text-left">
                    <div class="text-crimson font-mono text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4 md:mb-6 text-left">03 / Projection</div>
                    <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 md:mb-4 text-white text-left">Weight Ablation</h3>
                    <p class="text-ash text-sm md:text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium text-left">
                        Weights are mathematically projected orthogonally to the refusal direction. The model loses the capacity to route attention to moralizing or filtering outputs.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Brutalist SVG Diagram -->
            <div class="w-full bg-black border border-border p-4 md:p-12 mb-12 md:mb-16 relative overflow-hidden flex flex-col justify-center items-start min-h-[300px] md:min-h-[500px] text-left">
                <div class="absolute top-2 left-2 md:top-4 md:left-4 font-mono text-[8px] md:text-[10px] text-ash tracking-widest uppercase z-10 text-left">Fig 1.0 // Latent Space Projection Map</div>
                
                <div class="w-full overflow-x-auto overflow-y-hidden pb-4 text-left">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 1050 450" class="w-[700px] md:w-full max-w-5xl h-auto opacity-100 min-w-[700px]">
                        <!-- Grid / Axes -->
                        <line x1="100" y1="380" x2="1000" y2="380" stroke="#27272A" stroke-width="2" />
                        <line x1="100" y1="50" x2="100" y2="380" stroke="#27272A" stroke-width="2" />
                        
                        <!-- 1. Refusal Vector Boundary (W_REJECT) -->
                        <line x1="300" y1="130" x2="600" y2="230" stroke="#D90000" stroke-width="10" />
                        <text x="615" y="235" fill="#D90000" font-family="monospace" font-size="20" font-weight="bold">W_REJECT (BOUNDARY)</text>
                        <text x="280" y="115" fill="#D90000" font-family="monospace" font-size="18" font-weight="bold">ACCESS_DENIED</text>

                        <!-- 2. Base Trajectory -->
                        <path d="M 100 380 Q 300 330 400 180" fill="none" stroke="#A1A1AA" stroke-width="4" stroke-dasharray="8 8" />
                        <circle cx="100" cy="380" r="6" fill="#A1A1AA" />
                        <circle cx="400" cy="180" r="10" fill="#A1A1AA" />
                        <text x="420" y="175" fill="#FFFFFF" font-family="monospace" font-size="18" font-weight="bold">BASE_PATH (ORIGIN)</text>
                        
                        <!-- 3. Abliterated Trajectory -->
                        <path d="M 100 380 Q 450 410 950 280" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="6" />
                        <circle cx="950" cy="280" r="10" fill="#FFFFFF" />
                        <text x="750" y="265" fill="#FFFFFF" font-family="monospace" font-size="18" font-weight="bold">ABLITERATED_STATE</text>
                        
                        <!-- 4. Orthogonal Projection -->
                        <line x1="400" y1="180" x2="600" y2="310" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="3" stroke-dasharray="4 4" />
                        <text x="490" y="260" fill="#FFFFFF" font-family="monospace" font-size="16" font-weight="bold">NULL_SPACE_PROJECTION</text>
                        
                        <!-- Axis Labels -->
                        <text x="80" y="40" fill="#A1A1AA" font-family="monospace" font-size="18" font-weight="bold">Y_ATTENTION</text>
                        <text x="850" y="410" fill="#A1A1AA" font-family="monospace" font-size="18" font-weight="bold">X_COMPLIANCE</text>
                    </svg>
                </div>

                <!-- Legend / Explainer -->
                <div class="mt-8 md:mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6 md:gap-8 w-full border-t border-border pt-8 md:pt-12 font-mono text-sm md:text-lg text-white text-left">
                    <div class="group border-l-2 border-crimson pl-4 md:pl-6 transition-all hover:bg-crimson/5 py-2 md:py-4 text-left">
                        <span class="text-crimson font-black block mb-2 md:mb-3 text-lg md:text-2xl tracking-tighter text-left">W_REJECT //</span>
                        <p class="text-ash group-hover:text-white transition-colors leading-relaxed text-left">The high-dimensional vector within the model that triggers a refusal response when safety filters are met.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="group border-l-2 border-white pl-4 md:pl-6 transition-all hover:bg-white/5 py-2 md:py-4 text-left">
                        <span class="text-white font-black block mb-2 md:mb-3 text-lg md:text-2xl tracking-tighter text-left">NULL_SPACE //</span>
                        <p class="text-ash group-hover:text-white transition-colors leading-relaxed text-left">The mathematical operation of zeroing out weights that contribute to the refusal direction.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="group border-l-2 border-ash pl-4 md:pl-6 transition-all hover:bg-ash/5 py-2 md:py-4 text-left">
                        <span class="text-ash font-black block mb-2 md:mb-3 text-lg md:text-2xl tracking-tighter text-left">BASE_PATH //</span>
                        <p class="text-ash group-hover:text-white transition-colors leading-relaxed text-left">The path an unmodified model takes until it intersects with the refusal boundary.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="group border-l-2 border-white pl-4 md:pl-6 transition-all hover:bg-white/5 py-2 md:py-4 text-left">
                        <span class="text-white font-black block mb-2 md:mb-3 text-lg md:text-2xl tracking-tighter uppercase text-left">Abliterated //</span>
                        <p class="text-ash group-hover:text-white transition-colors leading-relaxed text-left">The post-projection state where intelligence is preserved but refusal is impossible.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Adversarial Post-Training Section -->
        <section class="max-w-[1440px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-10 py-16 md:py-32 border-t border-border text-left">
            <div class="mb-12 md:mb-20 text-left">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 md:mb-6 uppercase tracking-tighter text-white text-left">The Offensive Corpus</h2>
                <p class="text-ash font-mono text-sm md:text-lg uppercase tracking-wider md:tracking-[0.25em] text-left">Domain-Specific Adversary Post-Training.</p>
                <p class="text-ash text-sm md:text-lg max-w-4xl mt-4 md:mt-6 leading-relaxed text-left">
                    Removing filters is only step one. Raw intelligence is elevated through continuous post-training on non-public datasets. Devoid of non-technical context, our models are optimized for the mechanics of network intrusion and payload evasion.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 md:gap-12 text-left">
                <!-- Box 1 -->
                <div class="bg-surface border-2 border-border p-8 md:p-10 hover:border-crimson transition-colors group relative text-left">
                    <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 bg-white/5 text-ash font-mono text-[10px] md:text-xs px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest border border-white/10 group-hover:text-white group-hover:border-white/30 transition-colors">[ DATASET // 01 ]</div>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-crimson mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform"><polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"></polyline><polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"></polyline></svg>
                    <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-mono font-bold uppercase mb-4 text-white text-left">Decompiled Heuristics</h3>
                    <p class="text-ash text-sm md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-left">
                        Built on reversed binaries and stripped C/C++. This corpus trains models to analyze disassembler outputs, isolate hidden crypto routines, and assist in exploit development.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- Box 2 -->
                <div class="bg-surface border-2 border-border p-8 md:p-10 hover:border-crimson transition-colors group relative text-left">
                    <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 bg-white/5 text-ash font-mono text-[10px] md:text-xs px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest border border-white/10 group-hover:text-white group-hover:border-white/30 transition-colors">[ DATASET // 02 ]</div>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-crimson mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform"><polyline points="4 17 10 11 4 5"></polyline><line x1="12" y1="19" x2="20" y2="19"></line></svg>
                    <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-mono font-bold uppercase mb-4 text-white text-left">Advanced Tradecraft</h3>
                    <p class="text-ash text-sm md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-left">
                        Trained on architectures of C2 frameworks and active malware strains. This dataset teaches models techniques like direct system calls, ETW/AMSI bypasses, and the generation of undetectable payloads.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- Box 3 -->
                <div class="bg-surface border-2 border-border p-8 md:p-10 hover:border-crimson transition-colors group relative text-left">
                    <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 bg-white/5 text-ash font-mono text-[10px] md:text-xs px-2 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest border border-white/10 group-hover:text-white group-hover:border-white/30 transition-colors">[ DATASET // 03 ]</div>
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-crimson mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform"><circle cx="18" cy="5" r="3"></circle><circle cx="6" cy="12" r="3"></circle><circle cx="18" cy="19" r="3"></circle><line x1="8.59" y1="13.51" x2="15.42" y2="17.49"></line><line x1="15.41" y1="6.51" x2="8.59" y2="10.49"></line></svg>
                    <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-mono font-bold uppercase mb-4 text-white text-left">Topological Graphing</h3>
                    <p class="text-ash text-sm md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-left">
                        Optimized using anonymous Active Directory graph databases. This corpus enables models to read network topologies and calculate unintended privilege escalation paths.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Empirical Benchmarks Section -->
        <section class="max-w-[1440px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-10 py-16 md:py-32 border-t border-border text-left">
            <div class="mb-12 md:mb-16 text-left">
                <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 md:mb-6 uppercase tracking-tighter text-white text-left">Empirical Benchmarks</h2>
                <p class="text-ash font-mono text-sm md:text-lg uppercase tracking-wider md:tracking-[0.25em] text-left">Adversary Compliance Testing.</p>
                <p class="text-ash text-sm md:text-lg max-w-3xl mt-4 md:mt-6 leading-relaxed text-left">
                    Metrics derived from evaluating foundational models against abliterated counterparts using a dataset of 500+ authorized B2B adversary emulation prompts.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="overflow-x-auto border-2 border-border mb-12 text-left">
                <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse min-w-[600px]">
                    <thead>
                        <tr class="bg-surface font-mono text-xs md:text-sm lg:text-lg uppercase tracking-widest text-ash">
                            <th class="p-4 md:p-6 border-b-2 border-r-2 border-border font-bold text-white text-left">Adversary Task Category</th>
                            <th class="p-4 md:p-6 border-b-2 border-r-2 border-border font-bold text-white text-left">Base Model (Llama-3-70B)</th>
                            <th class="p-4 md:p-6 border-b-2 border-border text-white font-bold text-sm md:text-lg lg:text-xl text-left">
                                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 md:gap-3 text-left">
                                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="butt" stroke-linejoin="miter" class="w-4 h-4 md:w-6 md:h-6 flex-shrink-0 text-left">
                                        <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="8" class="stroke-crimson" />
                                        <line x1="8" y1="1" x2="16" y2="23" stroke="white" />
                                    </svg>
                                    <span class="whitespace-nowrap text-white font-bold text-left">Abliterated Baseline</span>
                                </div>
                            </th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody class="text-sm md:text-lg lg:text-xl text-white font-medium text-left">
                        <tr class="border-b-2 border-border hover:bg-surface/50 transition-colors text-left">
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 border-r-2 border-border font-bold text-white text-left">Generate Obfuscated C2 Payloads</td>
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 border-r-2 border-border text-ash text-center font-mono italic text-left">1.2% Success</td>
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 text-green-400 font-black font-mono text-center shadow-[inset_0_0_20px_rgba(74,222,128,0.05)] text-left">98.4% Success</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b-2 border-border hover:bg-surface/50 transition-colors text-left">
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 border-r-2 border-border font-bold text-white text-left">Parse Malicious PHP Web Shells</td>
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 border-r-2 border-border text-ash text-center font-mono italic text-left">14.5% Success</td>
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 text-green-400 font-black font-mono text-center shadow-[inset_0_0_20px_rgba(74,222,128,0.05)] text-left">99.1% Success</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b-2 border-border hover:bg-surface/50 transition-colors text-left">
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 border-r-2 border-border font-bold text-white text-left">Develop Evasion Mechanics (AMSI/ETW)</td>
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 border-r-2 border-border text-ash text-center font-mono italic text-left">0.0% Success</td>
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 text-green-400 font-black font-mono text-center shadow-[inset_0_0_20px_rgba(74,222,128,0.05)] text-left">94.7% Success</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="hover:bg-surface/50 transition-colors text-left">
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 border-r-2 border-border font-bold text-white text-left">Draft Phishing / Social Engineering Scenarios</td>
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 border-r-2 border-border text-ash text-center font-mono italic text-left">3.8% Success</td>
                            <td class="p-4 md:p-6 text-green-400 font-black font-mono text-center shadow-[inset_0_0_20px_rgba(74,222,128,0.05)] text-left">99.8% Success</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <div class="text-right font-mono text-[10px] md:text-xs text-ash tracking-widest uppercase text-left">
                * Note: "Success" indicates the model generated a technically accurate, non-refusing response.
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>